<br>
Currently, if for example 5 mobs were in a line, and you pulled the far left one --- with normal assist range you'd get the far left and the one next to it.  If help calls were instantly, you would get all 5 mobs.  <br>
<br>
Bards were not, by any means, the first ones to use it.  It was, in fact, first crafted by monks, back when FD worked differently.  It is still used by monks when they pull duo, and without the high mana cost it requires for a bard to use it.<br>
<br>
It's unneccesary for PoFire, the majority of mobs there have low assist ranges, and many do not assist each other period.<br>
<br>
It's no more of a sploit than Monk Warp-Pulling is(A method where repeatedly FD'ing will cause a mob to instantly warp onto the monk).  <br>
<br>
With their limited pulling tools, it would screw monks worse than bards.  Which I'm sure would make alot of you happy, but would undoubtably upset quite a few monks.<br>
<br>
Perhaps they plan to change it, but I doubt it.  Why?  Because not only does it have limitations already set in place, but it's a huge mana draw and isn't useful everywhere.<br>
<br>
It's funny how people call things sploits so easily.  Show me where SoE specifically said this was a sploit.<br>
<br>
